 Description:
 Longbow Hellfire (LBHF) missiles provide Littoral Combat Ship (LCS) firepower and offensive/defensive capabilities against large numbers of small manned and unmanned threats including fast attack craft,
 fast inshore attack craft, and aircraft, giving LCS the ability to protect the sea lanes and move a force quickly through a choke point or other strategic waterway. LCS equipped with the Surface Warfare Mission
 Package (SUW MP) will employ these missiles while escorting High Value Units (HVUs) or while conducting littoral operations. Navy procures and modifies LBHF from excess Army inventory for use on LCS.
 Army has notified Navy that additional LBHF transfers cannot be supported past FY26. Additionally, new production LBHF was last procured in 2005 and is being extended past its service with an uncertain end
 date These factors necessitate planning for transition to a replacement missile in FY27.

 Other Related Budgets: BLIs: OPN 1603 LCS SUW Mission Modules, RDT&E 0603596N LCS Mission Modules

 [P5 / Longbow Hellfire Missile]: The Longbow Hellfire missile is a fire and forget, millimeter-wave seeker missile for autonomous engagement. The Navy procures replacement in kind missiles from the Army
 inventory, completes shipboard modifications and certifications to deliver to the Fleet.

 [P5 / Ordnance Handling Equipment]: Ordnance Handling equipment procurements reflect a variety of tools, machinery, and devices used for handling, transportation, storage, and loading/unloading the missiles.
 Year-to-year, the specific equipment requirements change based on fleet needs and equipment deterioration/attrition. This equipment includes Lifting Caps, Lifting Straps, Missile Exhaust Containment Structure
 (MECS), MECS shipping brackets, MECS shipping frames, MEP test suite, MK210 stray voltage test sets, maintenance stands, tilt Fixtures, and MASS simulators. The increase in FY26 supports the additional
 handling equipment requirements. Evaluating ordnance equipment requirements across the FYDP.

 [P5 / Consulting Services]: Provides program management support, engineering and technical support, studies, analysis and evaluation on mission module systems.




