 Justification:
 This program, P-3A Mod F22031, Viability, is a new start.
 This program, P-3A Mod F22038, Helmet Mounted Display Cueing System (HMDCS), is a new start.

 The FY 2026 request for F-22 includes 977,526 thousand of discretionary and 100,000 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of 1,077,526 thousand. Mandatory funds would be used to procure 10
 Group B Pylon (Active) kits, 3 Group B Pylon (Guard) kits,10 Group B Tank (Active) kits, and 3 Group B Tank (Guard) kits. Information for this reconciliation request is provided in Section 20007 (Air Superiority)
 of the Reconciliation Exhibit.

 Modifications requesting FY26 funding are as follows: Reliability and Maintainability Program (Reliability & Maintainability); Link 16 (Capability Improvement); F119 Engine Modifications (Other); Trainers
 Modernization (Safety); Mode 5 Reply and Challenge (Capability Improvement); Viability (Capability Improvement); Sensor Enhancement (Capability Improvement); Low Drag Tanks and Pylons (Capability
 Improvement); and Controlled Reception Pattern Antenna (CRPA) (Capability Improvement). Further details are contained in the P-3A's.




