 Description:
 Massive Ordnance Penetrator (MOP) is a 30,000 lb class precision-guided penetrator designed to defeat hard and deeply buried targets.

 Funding is for non-recurring engineering, analysis and studies, integration, test, qualification, production readiness and operational readiness of engineering change proposals to resolve safety, reliability or other
 operational deficiencies, decrease weapon system cost, preserve future production capabilities and capacities, and meet Congressional, National Agency and Defense Department mandates.

 Funding may be used to address Diminishing Manufacturing Sources (DMS) issues. For example through studies, bridge buys, life of type buys, supplier/parts replacement, to include electronic components used
 commercially and in short supply, energetics, and qualification activities to preserve future production capabilities and capacities.

 This requirement supports performance of a full financial audit as required by title 10 U.S.C. Chapter 9A, Sec 240-D.

 Funding for this exhibit is contained in PE 0208030F, project 353190.




