 Description:
 The F-15EX is a new multirole-capable fighter jet based on the 2-seat F-15QA (Qatar) configuration, upgraded with advanced capabilities, including the Eagle Passive Active Warning Survivability System
 (EPAWSS) and USAF F-15 Continuous Delivery & Integration (CD&I) Operational Flight Program (OFP) software. The F-15EX platform provides significant operational flexibility, able to perform a wide range of
 mission sets with one or two aircrew.

 F-15EX aircraft have been procured over 6 Lots of aircraft from FY 2020 (Lot 1) to FY 2025 (Lot 6). F-15EX Modification supports retrofits to upgrade early F-15EX aircraft to a common production configuration
 (includes costs for kit procurement, installation, and other supporting requirements).

 The first 20 F-15EX aircraft (Lots 1 & 2) delivered with various configurations as new capabilities were cut into the production line.

 The FY 2026 request for F-15EX includes $0 thousands of discretionary and $286,700 thousands of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $286,700 thousands. The mandatory funds will be used for conformal
 fuel tanks (CFTs), aircraft modifications, and other supporting requirements. Further information for this reconciliation request is Provided in Section 20007 (Air Superiority) of the Reconciliation Exhibit.


 Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0207146F.

 Justification:
 F-15EX Modification includes retrofit efforts to upgrade the first 20 in-service aircraft (Lots 1 & 2) to a common production configuration. Retrofit scope includes procurement of Group A and Group B kit hardware,
 installation, and recurring and nonrecurring program support costs to update various components and wiring, enabling combat capability improvements. Specific retrofits include Multifunctional Information
 Distribution System - Joint Tactical Radio System Block Upgrade 3 (MIDS-JTRS BU3), Data Transfer Module II (DTM II), the ARC-210 Gen 6 radio, Anti-Jam GPS, weapons stores station wiring, cockpit pressure
 monitor and warning system, along with technical publication updates. Retrofit kits were procured with FY 2024 funding. FY 2026 funding supports kit installation.

 FY 2026 funding also provides for 18 sets of Conformal Fuel Tanks (CFTs), Bomb Rack Units, and associated costs as part of a post-production modification to support one operational squadron.

 Specifically, modification efforts include:

