 Description:
 The F-15 Eagle Passive Active Warning Survivability System (EPAWSS) replaces the legacy, functionally-obsolete F-15 Tactical Electronic Warfare System (TEWS). F-15 EPAWSS is a state-of-the-art electronic
 warfare system which includes electronic detection and identification, geolocation, electronic countermeasures (jamming), and countermeasures dispensing (chaff/flares). The EPAWSS upgrade will significantly
 improve the F-15's ability to deny, degrade, deceive, disrupt, and defeat radio frequency (RF) and electro-optical / infrared threat systems within contested and highly contested environments.

 The Air Force aligned F-15E EPAWSS procurement with the Air Force's Future Force Structure, which supports 99 EPAWSS-equipped F-15E aircraft. The Low-Rate Initial Production (LRIP) and Full Rate
 Production (FRP) phases overlap in years FY 2024 through FY 2026, providing a seamless transition to maintain the production schedule. Aircraft modifications will take place at the Contractor Modification
 Facility (CMF) in San Antonio, TX (SAT) and at the organic modification facility at Warner Robins Air Logistics Complex (WR-ALC), Robins AFB, GA. The LRIP / FRP contract overlap allowed for procurement of
 long-lead material required to maintain a consistent aircraft flow at both modification lines.

 Funding will be used to address ongoing Diminishing Manufacturing Sources (DMS) issues.

 EPAWSS' designed service life (DSL) aligns with the DSL of the aircraft.




