Justification:
Funding and budget data were revised to reflect execution actuals and updated program office projections based on the Full Rate Production proposal and contract award, which occurred in January 2025.

FY 2026 funding supports the following efforts:

- Installations: F-15E aircraft modifications occurring simultaneously between the Contractor Modification Facility (CMF) in San Antonio, TX (SAT) and the organic modification facility at Warner Robins Air
Logistics Complex (WR-ALC), Robins AFB, GA; the Program is continually assessing opportunities to maximize additional opportunities for organic installs at WR-ALC
- SEPM: System Engineering/Program Management covering both the LRIP and FRP contracts
- DMSMS: Monitoring and resolving Diminishing Manufacturing Sources/Material Shortages and/or obsolescence issues
- Production NRE: Software/operating system upgrades and applicable support equipment; efforts that increase maintenance data gathering capability
- Production Over & Above: Work discovered during modification that is not within EPAWSS scope but necessary to return aircraft to service
- ICS: Interim Contractor Support (ICS), to include Field Service Representatives (FSR), at operating locations
- CTR Repair Line Standup: Infrastructure investments to increase repair line capacity, thus avoiding impacts to concurrent hardware production
- Organic Install Tooling / Spt Equip: material required to maximize organic install capability at Warner Robins Air Logistics Complex
- SE/GFP Repair: Repair of Government Furnished Property (GFP); Supplemental tooling and support equipment (SE) for modification line and operating locations
- Data/Training: Updates to technical orders/manuals; technician and operator training
- OGCs/PMA/ECOs: Program Office requirements and change orders


The FY 2026 request was reduced by 0.290 million for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the Administration in alignment with Executive Order 14222,
"Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative.




