 Justification:
 This program, P-3A Mod 8578, C-130 SYSTEMS/STRUCTURE (PHASE II MODERNIZATION), is a new start.

 FY 2026 primary efforts include: C-130 Avionics Modernization Program (AMP) Increment 2 (Exhibit 8515), Center Wing Box (CWB) replacement (Exhibit 8578), NP2000 8-Bladed Propeller (Exhibit 3773), and
 Low Cost Modifications (Exhibit 99999X):

 - C-130H AMP Increment 2 will procure 21 kits between two procurement Lots: Lot 1 - 8 kits for installation in 1QFY2027, and Lot 2 - 13 kits for installation in 1QFY2028. The prime contractor has prepositioned
 8 kits, thus eliminating the 18-month procurement period for the Lot 1 kits. This action enables the program to procure the 13 Lot 2 kits upon MS C approval. The Lot 2 kits will be ready for installation upon
 completion of the Lot 1 kits.

 - CWB replacements will resume in 2026 with the procurement of 2 kits for installation in 2028. The contract supporting CWB procurement and installation will award in May 2026.

 - NP2000 8-Bladed Propeller completed installations on 90 C-130H aircraft in June 2025. The 2026 funding supports Interim Contractor Support for this modification.




