Justification:
FY26 procurement funding will concentrate on three major efforts: (1) initiate the integration and testing of Baseline 15, (2) continue the conversion of Baseline 12 aircraft into Baseline 14 aircraft, and (3) start the
conversion of Baseline 13 aircraft into Baseline 15 aircraft. Nine USAD RIVET JOINT aircraft are projected to receive the Baseline 14 configuration and eight USAF RIVET JOINT aircraft are projected to receive
the Baseline 15 configuration. During this same period, COMBAT SENT will complete the conversion of the Baseline 5 aircraft to Baseline 6, and the COBRA BALL complete integration and testing of Baseline
14. The COMBAT SENT and COBRA BALL baselines closely align with RIVET JOINT Baseline 14. Additionally, FY26 procurement will ensure integration and fielding updates to the RC-135 ground systems,
which include RIVET JOINT Ground Data Processing Systems (GDPS), Distributed Mission Shelters (DMS), Mission Crew Training Systems (MCTS), Airborne Capabilities Extension System (ACES) and
Operational Flight Trainers (OFT). The ground systems are upgraded to remain consistent with the fielded aircraft configurations to allow for training and qualification of the aircrew and maintenance personnel
assigned, plus verification and certification of software builds that are continuously modified to address the dynamic mission requirements of these weapons systems.

Due to the changing threat and rapidly evolving near peer electromagnetic combat environment, the acquisition program manager has the authority to redirect funding as necessary to meet current and emerging
Combatant Commander and/or Intelligence Community requirements to better meet the war fighting objectives.




