 Justification:
 FY26 funding will support:

 Mobility Air Forces (MAF): The modification and enhancement of high fidelity MAF aircrew training and support systems to meet combat readiness needs, to include efforts to ensure full employment of
 Distributed Mission Operations (DMO) capabilities.

 TDL Communications Capabilities: FY2026 efforts include: MIDS Modernization is a continuous technology development/acquisition strategy for robust interoperable communications for MIDS JTRS hosted
 waveforms. The current phase of this capability is a Link 16 enhancement to the MIDS JTRS known as Block Upgrade 3 (BU3). The modernized capability implements the required software and firmware updates
 necessary to meet the Joint Combatant Commander's prioritized requirements for Integrated Fire Control and Joint Tactical Grid information exchange requirements at the Tactical Edge. Upgrades to current
 fielded terminals began in FY23.

 Battlefield Airborne Communication Node (BACN): No FY2026 funding requested.

 FY26 efforts for this modification of Advanced Targeting Pods (ATPs) supports the procurement of various kits and kit upgrades as part of ATP-TI for both the LITENING and Sniper targeting pods to provide
 long-range target acquisition and expanded weapon delivery envelopes for greater aircraft survivability to include implementation and fielding of BE-CDL/Type 1 Encryption OSD Mandate (CM). ATP-TI Inc 1 is a
 continuation of ATP-Modernization Program (8674) and ATP-Sensor Enhancement (8675).

 The FY 2026 request was reduced by $0 million for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the Administration in alignment with Executive Order 14222,
 "Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative.




